    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 29, 3:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>804. The following is being sent to Paris.</p>
                <p>Number 26, January 28, 5 p.m. I received last night from the Provisional
                    Government a six hundred [<hi rend="italic">six?</hi>] page note, to the effect
                        <pb facs="0148" n="36" xml:id="pg_36"/> that it is both practically and
                    morally impossible to accept the proposition of a conference of Russian factions
                    which would include the Bolsheviki. The British Commissioner is telegraphing a
                    complete English translation<note n="37" xml:id="d25fn37">Not printed (Paris
                        Peace Conference 861.00/174).</note> to the British peace mission in Paris
                    and asking that a copy be furnished to you. The French Embassy has telegraphed a
                    summary to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
